SIMPLE: constantan
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: constantan
<hw>constantan</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a copper-nickel alloy composed of
approximately 55 per cent copper and 45 per cent nickel, with high
electrical resistance and a low temperature coefficient; it is used as
resistance wire and in thermocouples.</def> <note>It has a resistance
factor ⟦rho⟧ of 44.1 x 10<exp>-6</exp> ohm-cm at 0⟦deg⟧ C, in comparison
to the value 1.71 x 10<exp>-6</exp> ohm-cm for pure copper and 7.8 x
10<exp>-6</exp> ohm-cm for pure nickel. It is similar to the alloy
Eureka, which has a ⟦rho⟧ = 47 x 10<exp>-6</exp> ohm-cm. <au>Handbook of
Ch. 61</au>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Constantia</ent>⟦br⟧
